et search based on our\ncalculations. Our results highlight the comparable performance of optical and\nnear-IR spectrographs for most planet populations except for Earths and\ntemperate TESS planets which are more efficiently characterized in the near-IR.\nLastly, we present an online tool to the community to compute the total\nobserving times required to detect any transiting planet using a user-defined\nspectrograph.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Jul 2018 16:21:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-15"}
